point : if sanction be effective , their use be justified because they ultimately achieve a desired outcome . they cause financial pain to leader pressure them to reform . long term sanction on south africa be an effective policy . they cause the living standard in the country to deteriorate , however this ultimately lead to the right amount of pressure on the government for apartheid to be ended1 . economic restriction be first place on south africa in 1963 and be ultimately lift after the end of apartheid almost 30 year later . nelson mandela himself have state that sanction play a role in force the south african government to end apartheid2 . the success of sanction in the past have prevent the international community from take military action against certain state . due to prior success in south africa , sanction be an appropriate tool to push country towards reform while prevent military escalation . 1 foer , franklin 1996 , economic sanctions , slate . com , , accessed june 7 , 2011 . 3 2 laverty , alexander 2007 , impact of economic and political sanctions on apartheid , the africa file , accessed june 10 , 2011 . 13 
