point : arms embargo be a type of sanction that specifically target type of weapon . if a country be be particularly violent towards it people or at risk of civil war , arm embargo can be use to decrease the weapon available to the government or the people . in 1993 1994 an arm embargo be place on haiti by the united nations after a military coup by the group fadh the forces armarm√©es d haiti . forces be estimate to shrink from 6000 to 1000 by the time the us invade in 1994 thanks to the arm embargo 1 . preventing government from attain weapon can be the most effective way of stop government violence . if they don t have weapon to arm their military , civil war and genocide become more difficult to perpetrate . arms embargo have be successful and when use in conjunction with other policy action can be an effective way of address fear of civil war , ethnic cleansing , government violence , and coup . 
counterpoint : because of the size of the global community , and ease of communication and transport , most country can still attain necessary weapon and tool . as the world have globalize and information can be pass , attain , and hidden , with the click of a button , arm embargo be much more difficult to maintain . the un place an arm embargo on the sudan due to fear of ethnic cleanse carry out by the janjaweed , yet it be report that there be violation of the embargo on all side of the conflict . in fact , there be accusation back up by pictorial evidence that even after the arm embargo be put into place , china and russia , both member of the un security council , be sell weapon to the country1 . arms embargo often fall short of their goal . 1 bbc 2007 , china , russia deny weapon breach , accessed june 10 , 2011 . 15 
point : sanctions send a strong message to the people of a country that the western world be on their side and will not just remain compliant by deal with an oppressive regime a if it have do nothing wrong . part of what encourage people to stand up for their civil liberty be a feeling of support against their regime from outside actor . true reform need to come from pressure within and outside of the state a it do in south africa . the only way to incentivize internal pressure be by express support for civilian movement . in the case of the repressive government in myanmar , the lifting of sanction would be view a a betrayal by the myanmarese and would reverse any progress that sanction have help to achieve . the leader of the opposition movement , aung san suu kyi , in myanmar have call for a continuation of sanction , and in an act of support the us have complied1 . therefore sanction can be an important signal of support to a country's people , which make them more likely to stand up to their government and create the necessary internal pressure for reform . 1 colvin , jake and cox , simon 2007 , are economic sanctions good foreign policy ? , council on foreign relations , accessed june 10 , 2011 . 16 
